Bomet Senator Wilfred Lesan at the weekend defended Senate Speaker Ekwe Ethuro from accusations by opposition leaders that he did not allow for a fair voting during the debate on the election laws amendment bill.Lesan said, &ldquo;Our speaker has always acted professionally on the manner he handles both sides of the House. No senator voted illegally.&rdquo;He said the Speaker followed the Standing Orders and the Constitution to the letter in conducting House business. Speaking to the press in Bomet town yesterday, Lesan cited a case where a Jubilee senator voted against the bill and three senators from the opposition voted in support of the bill. He said that showed there was total freedom and independence. Lesan said the bill only allowed for complimentary way of voting in a case where electronic voting system fails.